port Policy This document outlines the cadet computing support policy  Computer Account Request The account request form must be completed  signed by user and department head and submitted to IT for network accounts  Computer Lab Rules Rules for computer labs Copyright This document outlines the copyright laws and users responsibilities to these laws  Data Breach Notification Policy This document outlines the notification requirements for VMI when a data breach occurs  Desktop Replacement Policy This document outlines the desktop replacement policy for faculty and staff computers  Digital Copyright Compliance Policy This policy addresses the downloading  copying and sharing of material  such as music  movies  games  and applications  for which the copyright holder has not given rights  Enterprise Technical Architecture This policy addresses two topics  facilities telecommunications infrastructure and telecommunications  Faculty Web Page Policy This policy was written by the Web Committee to ensure a consistent and professional appearance in consonance with the overall design of the VMI Web site  FERPA Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act FOIA Freedom of Information Act Hardware and Software Support Policy This document outlines the various levels of support for hardware and software  Microsoft Campus AgreementCampus agreement with Microsoft for software loaded on cadet  faculty and staff computers  Mission Critical Support Policy This document outlines computer systems designated as mission critical  Multimedia Classroom Support Policy This document outlines the support provided for multimedia classrooms  Password Policy This document outlines the VMI Password Policy  Password Descriptions This document outlines the restrictions which control the creation of passwords used for various accounts at VMI including the domain  Post View  and Colleague accounts  Policy on Use of Non VMI Owned Computing Devices to Telework This document refers to the policy on use of non VMI owned computing devices  Records Management The fundamental purpose of the VMI Records Management program is to ensure that Virginia s records retention requirements are fulfilled  as mandated by state law  to provide for the legal and efficient disposal of non permanent  non current records after the retention period has expired  and to preserve permanent  archival  records of enduring administrative  legal and or historical value  Removable Media Secure Use This document refers to the standards for secure use of removable data storage media  Security Awareness The Commonwealth of Virginia has developed an Information Technology Security Standard upon which VMI Security Awareness Policy is based  Software Copyright Policy This document outlines the software copyright policy  Software Installs in Labs This policy outlines the procedures required to install software in general purpose computer labs  Surplus Computer Policy Guidelines used by IT department for disposal of Computer equipment and electronic media  Surplus Computer Procedures This policy outlines the procedures to surplus computers  magnetic media and data  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 